{"title_page": "1986 Dunedin mayoral election", "text_new": "{{short description|New Zealand mayoral election}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use New Zealand English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 1986 Dunedin mayoral election\n| country            = New Zealand\n| flag_image         = Dunedin city coa.gif\n| type               = Presidential\n| ongoing            = no\n| previous_election  = 1983 Dunedin mayoral election\n| previous_year      = 1983\n| next_election      = 1989 Dunedin mayoral election\n| next_year          = 1989\n| election_date      = 11 October 1986\n| turnout            = 25,660\n| image1             = [[File:Clifford Skeggs.jpg|105px]]\n| candidate1         = [[Cliff Skeggs]]\n| party1             = Independent politician\n| popular_vote1      = 12,871\n| percentage1        = 50.15\n| image2             = [[File:No image.png|100px]]\n| candidate2         = Steve Alexander\n| party2             = New Zealand Labour Party\n| popular_vote2      = 7,064\n| percentage2        = 27.52\n| image3             = [[File:No image.png|100px]]\n| candidate3         = Bill Christie\n| party3             = Citizens'\n| color3             = 6495ED\n| popular_vote3      = 5,277\n| percentage3        = 20.56\n| title              = Mayor\n| before_election    = [[Cliff Skeggs]]\n| before_party       = \n| after_election     = [[Cliff Skeggs]]\n| after_party        = \n}}\n\nThe '''1986 Dunedin mayoral election''' was part of the New Zealand local elections held that same year. In 1986, elections were held for the [[Mayor of Dunedin]] plus other local government positions including twelve city councillors. The polling was conducted using the standard [[First-past-the-post voting|first-past-the-post]] electoral method.\n\n==Background==\nMayor [[Cliff Skeggs]] was re-elected for a record fourth term. Skeggs split from the Citizens' ticket but was re-elected as an independent candidate. Councillor Bill Christie stood as the official Citizens' candidate, polling third, with Labour's Steve Alexander placing second.\n\nElectoral reforms were implemented at the 1986 municipal elections, the method of electing councillors [[At-large|at large]] which had been used for decades was replaced with a [[Ward (electoral subdivision)|ward system]] of local electoral districts.<ref>{{cite news |author= |work =[[The Evening Post (Wellington)|The Evening Post]] |page= |title=Local elections on ward basis |date=9 October 1984 }}</ref>\n\n==Results==\nThe following table shows the results for the election:\n{{Election box begin | title=1986 Dunedin mayoral election<ref>{{cite news |work =[[Otago Daily Times]] |page=6 |title=Mayoral Voting |date=13 October 1986 |issue=37706 }}</ref>\n}}\n {{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n   |party      = Independent politician\n   |candidate  = [[Cliff Skeggs]]\n   |votes      = 12,871\n   |percentage = 50.15\n   |change     = -17.03\n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link|\n   |party      = New Zealand Labour Party\n   |candidate  = Steve Alexander\n   |votes      = 7,064\n   |percentage = 27.52\n   |change     = \n }}\n{{Election box candidate|\n   |party      = Citizens'\n   |color      = #6495ED\n   |candidate  = Bill Christie\n   |votes      = 5,277\n   |percentage = 20.56\n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box candidate with party link|\n   |party      = Independent politician\n   |candidate  = Murray Menzies\n   |votes      = 269\n   |percentage = 1.04\n   |change     = -2.69\n }}\n {{Election box informal|\n   |votes      = 179\n   |percentage = 0.69\n   |change     = -0.65\n }}\n {{Election box majority|\n   |votes      = 5,807\n   |percentage = 22.63\n   |change     = -16.82\n }}\n {{Election box turnout|\n   |votes      = 25,660\n   |percentage = \n   |change     = \n }}\n {{Election box end}}\n\n===Results by ward===\nCliff Skeggs polled the highest in all four of Dunedin's [[Ward (electoral subdivision)|electoral wards]].\n{{clear}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-bgcolor=\"#E6E6E6\"\n|Wards won by Skeggs\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right;\"\n! |\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=2 | Cliff Skeggs\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=2 | Steve Alexander\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=2 | Bill Christie\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=2 | Others\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" align=center | Ward\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 60%\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | #\n! scope=\"col\" align=center data-sort-type=\"number\" | %\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 60%\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | #\n! scope=\"col\" align=center data-sort-type=\"number\" | %\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 60%\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | #\n! scope=\"col\" align=center data-sort-type=\"number\" | %\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 60%\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | #\n! scope=\"col\" align=center data-sort-type=\"number\" | %\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 60%\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | #\n|-bgcolor=\"#E6E6E6\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\"|Central\n| '''3,052''' || '''51.01''' || 1,620 || 27.07 || 1,216 || 20.32 || 95 || 1.58 || 5,983\n|-bgcolor=\"#E6E6E6\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\"|East\n| '''3,409''' || '''51.17''' || 1,793 || 26.91 || 1,357 || 20.37 || 102 || 1.53 || 6,661\n|-bgcolor=\"#E6E6E6\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\"|North\n| '''3,201''' || '''44.56 '''|| 2,268 || 31.57 || 1,521 || 21.17 || 192 || 2.67 || 7,182\n|-bgcolor=\"#E6E6E6\"\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\"|West\n| 2,728 || 56.01 || 1,163 || 23.88 || 932 || 19.13 || 47 || 0.96 || 4,870\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" data-sort-value=\"Z\"|Total\n|data-sort-value=\"Z\"| '''12,871''' || '''50.15''' || 7,064 || 27.52 || 5,277 || 20.56 || 448 || 1.73 || 25,660\n|}\n\n==Ward results==\nCandidates