onard L. |title=The California Gold Rush and the Coming of the Civil War |publisher=Vintage Books Random House Inc. |location=New York |date=2007 |isbn=978-0-307-27757-2 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Rogers|first=Fred B.|title=Bear Flag Lieutenant: The Life Story of Henry L. Ford (1822\u20131860), with Some Related and Contemporary Art of Alexander Edouart|journal=California Historical Society Quarterly|publisher=University of California Press in association with the California Historical Society|volume=29|number=3|date=September 1950|pages=261\u201378|jstor=25156252\n|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Sabin|first=Edwin L.|title=Kit Carson Days, 1809\u20131868: Adventures in the Path of Empire |publisher=University of Nebraska Press|location=Lincoln|date=1995|volume=1|isbn=0-8032-9237-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=The Exploring Expedition to the Rocky Mountains in the Year 1842, and to Oregon and North California in the years 1843\u2013'44\n|url=https://archive.org/details/reportexploring00hallgoog|year=1845|publisher=[[Joseph Gales|Gales]] and [[William Winston Seaton|Seaton]]\n|location=Washington|quote=|ref=EERM}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=The Exploring Expedition to the Rocky Mountains, Oregon and California, to Which is Added A Description of the Physical Geography of California. With Recent Notices of the Gold Region from the Latest and Most Authentic Sources\n|url=https://archive.org/details/exploringexpedi01frgoog|year=1853|publisher=[[James Cephas Derby|Derby Orton & Mulligan]] |location=Buffalo|ref=EERM1853}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=The Life of Col. John Charles Fremont and His Narrative of Explorations and Adventures in Kansas, Nebraska, Oregon and California |last1=Fr\u00e9mont |first1=John Charles |last2=Smucker |first2=Samuel Mosheim\n|url=https://archive.org/details/lifecoljohnchar00smucgoog|year=1856 |publisher=Miller, Orton & Mulligan|location=New York and [[Auburn, New York|Auburn]]\n|ref=LifeJCF}}\n* {{cite book |last=Smith |first=Jean Edward